  <div id="main">
    <h1>Current Job Openings</h1>
                <h2> PeopleSoft Specialist: Albany, NY</h2>
      <p><strong>Due Date:</strong><br />
Saturday, September 17, 2016 2:30 AM</p>
<p><strong>Job Title:</strong><br />
 PeopleSoft Specialist</p>
<p><strong>Location:</strong><br />
Albany, NY</p>
<p><strong>Scheduled Work Hours:</strong><br />
Full Time - TBD</p>
<p><strong>Duration:</strong><br />
6</p>
<p><strong>Mandatory Skills:</strong><br />
Required Technical and Professional Expertise<Br /><Br />A  Bachelor's degree in computer science, information technology, or related field.<Br /><Br />Eight (8) years minimum application support experience with PeopleSoft Financial Management including Accounts Receivable, Billing, Accounts Payable and General Ledger.<Br />Four (4) years minimum application support experience with PeopleSoft Financial Management release 9.1.<Br />Excellent verbal and written English communication skills.<Br /><Br />Ability to communicate with business users and management on issues impacting PeopleSoft Financial Management operations functionality along with recommendations for corrective actions.<Br />Strong organizational, administrative and problem solving skills; proficient with analytic and quality assurance techniques.<Br /><Br />Experience with PeopleSoft Configuration Manager and Data Mover. Experience using Oracle Metalink.<Br />Experience in PeopleSoft Administration including project and code migration, patching and problem reporting.<Br />Developer experience utilizing various PeopleSoft programming languages SQL, SQR, PeopleCode and Application Engine and tools in Application Designer.<Br />Experience monitoring inbound and outbound external interfaces.<Br /><Br />Ability to troubleshoot all areas of the PeopleSoft architecture including financial applications, Process Scheduler, WebServer, Windows Schedulers, network, AIX and Oracle database.<Br />Experience as the primary PeopleSoft Security administrator for PeopleSoft Financials. Ability to design, develop, test, and implement PeopleSoft security.</p>
<p><a href="mailto:resume@gcomsoft.com?subject=GCOM Software Job Application: DOH PeopleSoft Specialist&body=(Please remember to attach your resume to this message)" class="button-orange">Apply for this job</a></p>
      <p><a href="/page/current-job-openings-43.html">&laquo; Back to Current Job Openings</a></p>
